begin_memory_text: I don't remember the topic. We sort of just started talking about pets, I think. I am honestly having trouble remembering what topic was started with. All I can say for sure is that it was still enjoyable.
middle_memory_text: We discussed various topics. Pets, life, travel, politics, the economy....We covered a variety of topics individually and blended together.
end_memory_text: The end of the conversation seemed mostly focused on politics and the economy. Towards the very end, we discussed conversations and like-minded discussion groups. We even got around to introducing each other with our names.
rest_of_day_open: I expect the rest of my week to go quite well. I will definitely look into a few things that were discussed in this most recent conversation. I hope to accomplish a few productive things and make use of my time. The ultimate goal is to do more this week than I did last week.
critical_positive: I think almost everything worked well. Our conversation went very well and was very fluid. We discussed a range of topics that we both seemed to respond well to. Neither of us seemed to have an extreme opposition to each other's viewpoints. There were no noticeable gaps in the conversation and no awkward silences.
critical_negative: There wasn't much that didn't work well. I feel like I may have talked longer or over them at certain times, so I think I could have been better about sharing the talking time more. I don't recall there having been any real negative or disruptive moments in the conversation.

begin_memory_text: My cat started playing with the webcam wire so I had to take him out of the room and that got us started on talking about our cats. That lasted a while and then segued into Adam telling me about a road trip where he found a kitten.
middle_memory_text: In the middle we were talking abot a road trip Adam took and I asked where he is at and we talked about his region for awhile, and then Northern Michigan, where we both had visisted or lived in earlier in our lives.
end_memory_text: Toward the end we talked about Covid relief and the economy and what might happen with a future stimulus, including with or without a continued Trump presidency.  Adam talked about travel and other cultures and religions, and after awhile I brought up Humanism, especially the Zoom meetups by the Minnesota and Phoenix humanist groups.  It sounded like he liked learning and would like to talk with more people, so I thought he might find those types of virtual meetups rewarding.
rest_of_day_open: Ah, the weekly question rears its head once more. For the next several days I currently have one meetup scheduled where I get to talk with my friends from the humanist society of Phoenix on Zoom for 3 hours. That is a weekly highlight.  Otherwise I have lots of unscheduled time and will be enjoying the cooler Arizona weather as I work in my yard.
critical_positive: Adam was interesting and was good at telling stories.  I mean true events, but related in a smooth, clear, and interesting fashion.  I enjoyed talking with him and even when I noticed the time had passed 30 minutes I decided to keep going as long as he wanted, or until it was time for me to tend to my chores and head out to pickup my grocery order.
critical_negative: Adam kind of jumped in telling me in detail about his 6 cats before we even introduced ourselves.  I didn't mind, but I think he missed that an overview and a briefer dive into details might be more appropriate at the very beginning of a conversation in which 2 people just met for the first time. I asked his name right near the end, as it still seemed polite, and I rather like writing these summaries with peoples' names rather than using pronouns.
